{0 Completion (wikilink suggestions)}

Suggest note names, headings, and block IDs as the user types inside
wikilink brackets.

{1 Activation}

The server advertises [completionProvider] with trigger characters
[[\[] ].  Completion is requested via [textDocument/completion].

{1 Trigger context}

Completion activates when the cursor is inside an incomplete wikilink:

{ul
  {- [[\[<cursor>]]] — typing the note name}
  {- [[\[note#<cursor>]]] — typing a heading or block-ID fragment}
  {- [![\[<cursor>]]] — embed link, same behavior}
}

Detection: scan backwards from the cursor for an unmatched [[\[] ] (or
[![\[] ]) on the same line.  If found, the text between [[\[] ] and the
cursor is the {e prefix}.

{1 Completion modes}

{2 Note name completion}

When the prefix contains no [#], suggest note names from the vault
index.

{ul
  {- Each indexed file yields one completion item.}
  {- [label]: the note's shortest unambiguous name (the same name the
     vault resolver would accept).}
  {- [detail]: the full relative path, e.g. ["folder/note.md"].}
  {- [filterText]: the note name, so the client can narrow as the
     user types.}
  {- [kind]: [CompletionItemKind.File].}
}

Items are sorted alphabetically by label.

{2 Fragment completion}

When the prefix contains [#], the text before [#] identifies the target
note (or the current file if empty, as in [[\[#<cursor>]]]).  The text
after [#] is the fragment prefix.

Suggestions come from the target file's AST:

{ul
  {- {b Headings}: one item per heading.
     [label] is the heading text, [filterText] is the slug,
     [kind] is [CompletionItemKind.Reference].
     [insertText] is the slug (e.g. [section-one]).}
  {- {b Block IDs}: one item per block ID.
     [label] is [^blockid],
     [kind] is [CompletionItemKind.Reference].}
}

If the target note cannot be resolved, no fragment suggestions are
returned.

{1 Completion item shape}

{t
  | Field      | Note name mode           | Fragment mode            |
  |------------|--------------------------|--------------------------|
  | label      | shortest unambiguous name | heading text or [^id]    |
  | detail     | full relative path       | —                        |
  | filterText | note name                | slug or block ID         |
  | insertText | note name                | slug or [^blockid]       |
  | kind       | File                     | Reference                |
}

{1 Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Cursor not inside [[\[...]]]}: no completions.}
  {- {b Empty vault}: empty completion list.}
  {- {b Ambiguous note name in fragment mode}: resolve using vault
     resolution rules (same as go-to-definition); suggest fragments
     from the first candidate.}
  {- {b Markdown links}: completion inside [()] is not provided (wikilink
     brackets only).}
}
